DNS Configuration Lab using Cisco Packet Tracer
This project demonstrates the configuration and testing of the Domain Name System (DNS) in a simulated network environment using Cisco Packet Tracer. The lab shows how DNS translates domain names into IP addresses, allowing devices to communicate using human-readable names instead of numerical IP addresses.

Features -
1. DNS Server configuration
IP addressing setup
2. Client-PC network configuration
3. DNS record creation
4. Domain name resolution testing
5. Network connectivity verification using Ping and Web Browser

Tools Used -
1. Cisco Packet Tracer
2. Networking Devices (PCs, Switches, Routers, Servers)
3. Learning Outcomes
4. Understand the working of DNS.
5. Configure a DNS server in Packet Tracer.
6. Create and manage DNS records.
7. Test domain name resolution in a network.
8. Troubleshoot basic DNS-related issues.
